sql:
SELECT log_gdp_per_capita 
FROM happiness_data
WHERE log_gdp_per_capita > (
    SELECT AVG(log_gdp_per_capita) FROM happiness_data
) AND log_gdp_per_capita IS NOT NULL;

external_knowledge:
- More prosperous parts: refers to countries with higher life ladder scores and social support; 
- Generally doing okay in life: implies a life ladder score > 6;
- Expect to live a healthy life for over 70 years: indicates healthy life expectancy > 70.

sql:
SELECT AVG(life_ladder) AS average_life_ladder
FROM happiness_data
WHERE country_id = 0 AND year = 2022;

external_knowledge:
- 'Beacons of hope' metaphorically refer to the countries;
- 'Cast a glow brighter than a score of six on the ladder of life' is a metaphorical way to describe having an average life ladder score greater than 6;
- The 'ladder of life' is a metaphorical representation of the quality of life as measured by the life ladder score.

- 'Measure of happiness' refers to the life ladder score;
- The 'respective categories' are defined by the combination of region, sub-region, and income group;
- A higher life ladder score indicates a higher measure of happiness.

